      "id": 18,
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### Reading this dashboard\n\n**Time to Attention** = projected days until an object reaches **80%** of its capacity, computed as `(0.80\u00b7capacity \u2212 usage) \u00f7 daily_growth`. Daily growth is the `deriv()` of usage over the **$growth_window** window, evaluated against **VictoriaMetrics** (90-day retention).\n\n- **Projections need history.** A 14-day window needs ~14 days of accumulated data to be meaningful. Right after a fresh VictoriaMetrics start, set the window to **7d** to get earlier (noisier) estimates.\n- **Linear extrapolation.** Assumes recent growth continues at a constant rate \u2014 a planning aid, not a guarantee. Bursty workloads will swing.\n- **`3yr+`** means the object is projected to take more than 3 years (1095 days) \u2014 effectively not a concern.\n- **Flat or shrinking** objects are floored to a 1 byte/day growth, so they land at `3yr+`.\n\n**Thresholds:** the 80% warning level here is a dashboard constant. It is independent of the `alerts.*WarningPct` values in `values.yaml` (storage dashboards are delivered as raw JSON and cannot read Helm values). Keep them aligned if you change the alert thresholds.\n\n**Planes covered:** Longhorn nodes, **PVC filesystems (true fill % from kubelet volume stats \u2014 replica/snapshot-independent)**, MinIO tenants, DirectPV nodes, node root filesystems, and customer Longhorn soft-cap quotas (the Customer Quota rows appear only once a customer has `quotaGi.longhorn` set)."
      },
      "title": "Methodology & caveats",
      "type": "text"
    }
